# Store

`src/store/graph.ts` is a single Zustand store that holds all app state. There is no other global state.

## Shape

```ts
interface GraphState {
  nodes: Node<ConceptNodeData>[];
  edges: Edge[];
  selected: { kind: "node" | "edge"; id: string } | null;
  settings: NessoSettings;
  tutorialDone: boolean;
  relationTypesPanelOpen: boolean;
  viewports: Record<string, { x: number; y: number; zoom: number }>;
  currentGraphId: string;
  graphList: { id: string; name: string; updatedAt: number }[];
  // ... mutations below
}
```

Persistence: Zustand `persist` (`nesso`) rehydrates `settings`, `tutorialDone`, `relationTypesPanelOpen`, `currentGraphId`, `graphList`, and `viewports`. Graph node/edge payloads live in IndexedDB (`src/store/db.ts`); the app loads the active graph via `loadGraph` and writes with `saveCurrentGraph` (debounced from `useAutoSave`).

## Mutations

| Method                            | Effect                                                                                                                             |
| --------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `onNodesChange` / `onEdgesChange` | React Flow change handlers (move, resize, remove)                                                                                  |
| `updateNodeData(id, patch)`       | Partial update of a node's `ConceptNodeData`                                                                                       |
| `addNode(x?, y?)`                 | Inserts a new concept node, selects it, returns its id                                                                             |
| `deleteNode(id)`                  | Removes node and all its incident edges, clears selection if needed                                                                |
| `addEdge(source, target, type)`   | Inserts a `'nesso'` edge with `sourceHandle` / `targetHandle` matching concept node handles (`out` / `in`), selects it, returns id |
| `updateEdgeType(id, type)`        | Changes the relation type on an existing edge                                                                                      |
| `deleteEdge(id)`                  | Removes edge, clears selection if needed                                                                                           |
| `setSelected(sel)`                | Sets selection (or `null` to deselect)                                                                                             |
| `setSetting(key, value)`          | Updates a single `NessoSettings` field                                                                                             |
| `completeTutorial`                | Sets `tutorialDone` to true (dismisses onboarding; persisted)                                                                      |
| `setRelationTypesPanelOpen(open)` | Shows or hides the left “Relation types” / edge legend panel (persisted)                                                           |
| `toggleRelationTypesPanel`        | Toggles the relation types panel open/closed (persisted)                                                                           |
| `saveViewport(id, vp)`            | Stores last React Flow viewport for a graph id (persisted)                                                                         |
| `loadGraphList`                   | Refreshes `graphList` from IndexedDB                                                                                               |
| `loadGraph(id)`                   | Switches active graph: loads nodes/edges from IndexedDB; selects `id`                                                              |
| `saveCurrentGraph`                | Writes current nodes/edges for `currentGraphId` to IndexedDB                                                                       |
| `createGraph(name)`               | New empty graph; saves, switches to it, returns id                                                                                 |
| `renameGraph(id, name)`           | Updates graph name in IndexedDB and `graphList`                                                                                    |
| `deleteGraph(id)`                 | Removes record from IndexedDB; if active, switches to another graph                                                                |

## Selectors

Two named selectors are exported from `graph.ts`:

```ts
export const selectedNodeSelector = (s: GraphState) =>
  Node<ConceptNodeData> | null;
export const selectedEdgeSelector = (s: GraphState) => Edge | null;
```

Use these in components — do not inline the selection look-up logic.

## Rules

- Do not add local `useState` for data that belongs in the store (node text, edge type, selection).
- New store fields go in `GraphState`; initialise them in the `create(...)` call.
- Selectors that are used in more than one component should be exported from `graph.ts`, not defined inline per component.
